				  lohit-nepali
Current Version :- 2.94.2

* Wed Apr 26 2017 Pravin Satpute <psatpute@redhat.com> - 2.94.2
- Added appstream metadata file io.pagure.lohit.nepali.font.metainfo.xml

* Thu Mar 02 2017 Pravin Satpute <psatpute@redhat.com> - 2.94.1
- Updated .fea file and remove .mr glyphs from sfd files.
- PR for python2 to 3 from ShaguftaMethwani and mandarvaze.
- Updated Makefile to call script from fontforge rather than python.

* Wed May 14 2014 Pravin Satpute <psatpute@redhat.com> - 2.94.0
- Porting from Devanagari to Nepali
- Positioning lookup clean-up.
- Improved grid fitting(GASP) table.
- Renamed anchors to DVAnchor.
- Using glyph reference (copy reference) instead of whole glyph points.
- Auto test integrated with Makefile ($make test).
- Resolved #32: "सर्व्हिस does not render correctly"
- Resolved #33: "improper rendering for word : "मञ्यांच्या""

* Mon Dec 23 2013 Pravin Satpute <psatpute@redhat.com> - 2.93.0
- Forked Lohit Devanagari 2.93.0 for Nepali
- Will output default Marathi locale specific ligatures and characters.
- For improvements in Lohit Devanagari see
https://raw.github.com/pravins/lohit/master/devanagari/ChangeLog

* Fri Dec 21 2012 Pravin Satpute <psatpute@redhat.com> - 2.5.3
- corrected glyph class of "asciicircum"
- Dropping RFN from OFL.txt
- Switched to 2.5.3 to match version with family

* Thu Mar 22 2012 Pravin Satpute <psatpute@redhat.com> - 2.5.1.1
- corrected u0938 "स" character shape, #799004
- resolved issues of improper rendering in Nepali locale

* Wed Feb 29 2012 Pravin Satpute <psatpute@redhat.com> - 2.5.1
- This is fork of Lohit Devanagari specifically for marathi language
- Using Lohit Devanagari with mr_IN locale is equivalent to this font
- for older changes see Changelog of Lohit Devanagari
